n references and concerns. Ultimately, Albuqerque urges historians to question received concepts, such as regions and regionalism, to reveal their artifice and abandon static categories in favor of new, more granular understandings.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh1 aGreen, James N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMetz, Jerry Dennis08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822376071zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822376071423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822376071.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles